01:09:37.479 --> 01:09:39.118
Thor?

01:09:40.120 --> 01:09:42.714
Damn. Heather and Thor?

01:09:44.640 --> 01:09:46.232
Damn.

01:09:50.080 --> 01:09:52.719
I'm worried about Thor.
It's hard for us to imagine

01:09:52.920 --> 01:09:55.195
how upsetting it is
not knowing the colours.

01:09:55.400 --> 01:09:57.311
It's impossible for me to imagine.

01:09:57.520 --> 01:10:00.398
When Thor sees a rainbow,
it's so much gibberish to him.

01:10:00.600 --> 01:10:03.637
There was one this afternoon.
Oh, my gosh, he took it hard.

01:10:03.840 --> 01:10:05.910
Recently, there was a parade
in the city

01:10:06.120 --> 01:10:09.271
where the marchers carried
rainbow-coloured flags and banners.

01:10:09.480 --> 01:10:11.835
Thor was so upset.
He had no idea what it meant.

01:10:12.040 --> 01:10:13.439
What kind of retard is he?

01:10:13.640 --> 01:10:15.790
See, that's the conclusion
people jump to.

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:17.592
Well, it is somewhat understandable.

01:10:17.800 --> 01:10:19.518
Not if you knew the full story.

01:10:19.720 --> 01:10:20.789
What's the full story?

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:22.911
You know how parents
love bragging

01:10:23.120 --> 01:10:25.634
about how precocious
their children are?

01:10:25.840 --> 01:10:28.115
Thor's parents
had become precocity addicts,

01:10:28.320 --> 01:10:31.198
constantly needing
an ever-greater precocity fix.

01:10:31.400 --> 01:10:34.790
He should've entered kindergarten.
They pushed him into first grade.

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:37.036
"Thor skipped a grade,"
they could tell.

01:10:37.240 --> 01:10:40.915
What Thor's parents failed to consider
is the work done in nursery school.

01:10:41.120 --> 01:10:44.157
Key being the study of colours.
I suppose they just assumed

01:10:44.360 --> 01:10:46.635
that colours are knowledge
people pick up.

01:10:46.840 --> 01:10:49.035
Like, for example,
not stepping on sidewalk cracks.

01:10:50.400 --> 01:10:52.152
What's that?

01:10:52.360 --> 01:10:54.191
I think Rose is sleeping.

01:10:55.720 --> 01:10:57.119
Am I boring?

01:10:57.320 --> 01:10:58.673
No, not at all.

01:10:59.200 --> 01:11:02.875
When you have problems, it's great
to hear someone else's idiotic ones.

01:11:03.080 --> 01:11:04.798
Please go on.

01:11:05.840 --> 01:11:07.990
Wow.
What?

01:11:08.200 --> 01:11:11.192
What you said about depressed
people being mean, you werert joking.

01:11:11.400 --> 01:11:13.868
I'm sorry, you're right. Please go on.

01:11:14.720 --> 01:11:16.039
No.

01:11:16.240 --> 01:11:20.153
I'm sorry. You know how I am.
Please continue.

01:11:22.920 --> 01:11:25.593
Thor decided he absolutely
had to learn all the colours.

01:11:25.800 --> 01:11:27.631
Both primary and mixed.

01:11:27.840 --> 01:11:31.230
He's been hitting the books hard,
and thought he'd mastered them.

01:11:31.440 --> 01:11:34.000
Then, in town, he said,
"That traffic light's blue. "

01:11:34.200 --> 01:11:36.077
I had to say, "No, it's green. "

01:11:36.280 --> 01:11:37.269
He was really upset.

01:11:37.480 --> 01:11:38.549
Oh, hi, Lily.

01:11:39.200 --> 01:11:40.189
Hi.

01:11:40.400 --> 01:11:42.197
We were worried about you.

01:11:45.480 --> 01:11:47.675
<i>I can't bear this tension with Lily.</i>

01:11:47.880 --> 01:11:50.235
It's terrible to have the group
divided this way.

01:11:50.440 --> 01:11:51.873
Better not next to Robertson.

01:11:53.280 --> 01:11:54.599
What?

01:11:54.800 --> 01:11:56.472
Didrt you hear?

01:11:56.680 --> 01:11:58.989
Ed students have been going
up to the roof

01:11:59.200 --> 01:12:01.031
and throwing themselves off.

01:12:02.640 --> 01:12:04.915
But it's only two storeys.
Yes, I know.

01:12:05.120 --> 01:12:08.271
It's terrible. Not high enough to kill,
but high enough to maim.

01:12:08.480 --> 01:12:11.040
And particularly dangerous
for anyone below.

01:12:11.240 --> 01:12:13.595
I've got to forget about Fred.

01:12:14.080 --> 01:12:15.399
But you really liked him.

01:12:15.600 --> 01:12:20.515
This whole thing of a person meeting
someone else first, it's so arbitrary.

01:12:20.720 --> 01:12:25.589
It's terrible and cruel.
I have to say, I was wrong about Fred.

01:12:25.800 --> 01:12:28.075
I thought he was a playboy
or operator type.

01:12:28.280 --> 01:12:32.319
In fact, he's just another guy rendered
helpless by the attentions of a pretty girl.

01:12:32.520 --> 01:12:35.193
Cary! No, don't!
I love you!

01:12:36.560 --> 01:12:38.232
Why did you do that?
Oh, my God!

01:12:38.440 --> 01:12:40.158
Cary, I love you!

01:12:41.880 --> 01:12:44.678
Isn't the Ed School
essentially a teacher's college?

01:12:44.880 --> 01:12:45.915
Yeah.

01:12:46.120 --> 01:12:48.429
If they can't even
destroy themselves,

01:12:48.640 --> 01:12:50.835
how are they going to teach
America's youth?

01:12:51.040 --> 01:12:54.715
# It's just that my happiness
Finally commences #

01:12:54.920 --> 01:12:57.480
# Things are looking up #

01:12:57.680 --> 01:13:00.717
# I've been looking
The landscape over #

01:13:00.920 --> 01:13:04.276
# And it's covered
With four-leaf clover #

01:13:04.480 --> 01:13:06.994
# Oh, things are looking up #

01:13:07.200 --> 01:13:11.398
# Since love looked up at me #

01:13:14.480 --> 01:13:17.233
# But no more
Will I be the mourner #

01:13:17.440 --> 01:13:20.159
# For I've certainly turned
the corner ##

01:13:20.360 --> 01:13:23.193
What do you think you're doing?
Sorry. Did I disturb you?

01:13:23.400 --> 01:13:25.960
Why are you wearing tap shoes?
You out of your mind?

01:13:26.320 --> 01:13:29.118
I think that's pretty clear.
I'm so sick of that.

01:13:29.320 --> 01:13:30.833
Oh, really? I think it's cute.

01:13:31.040 --> 01:13:35.113
Since you won't be treating us to
one of your incompetent tap routines,

01:13:35.320 --> 01:13:39.029
why don't you take those things off?
No. We'll do the routine. Rose.

01:13:39.240 --> 01:13:42.550
Madge wants to see the routine.
I don't want to see your routine.

01:13:42.760 --> 01:13:45.149
I asked you to take those off.
We need a break.

01:13:45.360 --> 01:13:46.395
Just briefly, please.

01:13:46.600 --> 01:13:49.319
It's helpful to have an audience.
Rose, the music.

01:13:49.520 --> 01:13:51.112
I'm gonna report you.

01:14:18.120 --> 01:14:19.633
Suzanne.

01:14:19.840 --> 01:14:23.992
For me, it'd be Madame Curie,
Simone de Beauvoir,

01:14:24.200 --> 01:14:26.555
and Margaret Sanger.
Good.

01:14:27.480 --> 01:14:28.674
Violet.

01:14:28.880 --> 01:14:30.677
I would say

01:14:31.440 --> 01:14:33.476
Richard Strauss,
Roderick Charleston,

01:14:33.680 --> 01:14:35.398
and Chubbard Checker.

01:14:35.600 --> 01:14:39.673
Richard Strauss? The composer?
Yes, that was one of his posts.

01:14:39.880 --> 01:14:43.111
I'm not familiar with the others.
Could you tell us who they are?

01:14:43.320 --> 01:14:46.471
Yes. Each one of these men
started an international dance craze.

01:14:46.680 --> 01:14:49.831
Richard Strauss, the waltz.
Roderick Charleston, the Charleston.

01:14:50.040 --> 01:14:51.837
Chubbard Checker,
known as Chubby,

01:14:52.040 --> 01:14:53.712
the dance we know as the twist.

01:14:53.920 --> 01:14:56.036
Why do you consider
a dance craze important?

01:14:56.240 --> 01:14:59.391
Dance crazes enance
and elevate the human experience,

01:14:59.600 --> 01:15:01.636
bringing together
millions of people

01:15:01.840 --> 01:15:04.638
in a joyous celebration
of our God-given faculties,

01:15:04.840 --> 01:15:07.354
and passing these modes
of physical expression

01:15:07.560 --> 01:15:10.711
down through the generations.
Though not so much anymore.

01:15:10.920 --> 01:15:13.388
I thought...
Well, I assumed that the Charleston

01:15:13.600 --> 01:15:15.909
was named after
the city of Charleston.

01:15:16.120 --> 01:15:18.918
No. Though that misconception
is quite widely held.

01:15:19.120 --> 01:15:21.156
It was Roderick Charleston.

01:15:21.360 --> 01:15:24.238
Usually, behind some
great creative phenomenon,

01:15:24.440 --> 01:15:26.715
there's a person, not a town.

01:15:26.920 --> 01:15:29.673
This is so exciting.
It's really great, isn't it?

01:15:29.880 --> 01:15:32.155
Hey, could you guys help?
Sure. What's up?

01:15:32.360 --> 01:15:33.759
We need help packing soap,

01:15:33.960 --> 01:15:36.349
which we'll distribute
to Doar Dorm residents.

01:15:36.560 --> 01:15:37.629
Cool.

01:15:37.840 --> 01:15:40.877
What would you say are effective
means to fight depression?

01:15:41.080 --> 01:15:44.277
Maybe some of your DU brothers
have an idea?

01:15:45.880 --> 01:15:49.429
Uh... Beer?
No. Beer's a downer.

01:15:49.640 --> 01:15:53.519
Cocktails. Hard liquor and spirits
is what really gives you a lift.

01:15:53.720 --> 01:15:55.199
It's interesting what you say.

01:15:55.400 --> 01:15:58.710
My cousin Jay is a medical officer
in Philadelphia.

01:15:58.920 --> 01:16:00.148
He says that alcoholism,

01:16:00.360 --> 01:16:03.511
by which I mean chronic,
excessive consumption of alcohol,

01:16:03.720 --> 01:16:06.757
is the primary self-administered
treatment for depression.

01:16:06.960 --> 01:16:08.154
Cool.
No.

01:16:08.360 --> 01:16:10.590
It leaves you much worse off
than before.

01:16:10.800 --> 01:16:13.360
Oh, no, not me.
I just boot and then I feel fine.

01:16:13.560 --> 01:16:17.553
By "boot" do you mean vomit?
Yes.

01:16:17.760 --> 01:16:21.912
No. None of the effective anti-suicide
treatments involve vomiting.

01:16:23.200 --> 01:16:25.430
Hygiene?
Exactly.

01:16:25.640 --> 01:16:26.834
It's very important.

01:16:27.040 --> 01:16:29.315
That's why we have such hope
in the wonder bar.

01:16:29.520 --> 01:16:31.078
Do you know its scent?

01:16:35.320 --> 01:16:39.359
Wow.
Transformative, we think.

01:16:41.360 --> 01:16:44.193
This is so exciting.
When should we go over there?

01:16:44.400 --> 01:16:47.039
I don't think there's any rush.
I'd like to go soon.

01:16:47.240 --> 01:16:51.028
Doar Dorm has the highest fatality
rate, as well as the worst hygiene.

01:16:51.240 --> 01:16:52.229
Highest suicide rate.

01:16:52.440 --> 01:16:55.671
Fatality rate. It's uncertain
what percentage were intentional

01:16:55.880 --> 01:16:58.997
and how many were just due
to unawareness of gravity's laws.

01:16:59.200 --> 01:17:02.715
I can just see those guys getting
the gold packages, opening them,

01:17:02.920 --> 01:17:05.115
and finding
the good-smelling soap inside.

01:17:05.320 --> 01:17:07.515
The cute packaging
should prove irresistible.

01:17:07.720 --> 01:17:10.792
And once clean, they'll start
to see the world with new eyes.

01:17:11.000 --> 01:17:12.433
The change could be dramatic.

01:17:12.640 --> 01:17:15.473
Doar Dorm
could soon become Dior Dorm.

01:17:16.280 --> 01:17:18.953
I doubt that,
to be perfectly, absolutely honest.

01:17:19.160 --> 01:17:21.674
I love the idea. Dior Dorm.

01:17:21.880 --> 01:17:24.440
I adore optimism,
even when it's completely absurd.

01:17:24.640 --> 01:17:27.996
Perhaps especially then.
Great. Ready? Let's go.

01:17:30.080 --> 01:17:31.479
Let's hurry.

01:17:31.680 --> 01:17:34.035
Let's not get our hopes up too high,
Heather.

01:17:34.240 --> 01:17:37.994
No, you said yourself,
the wonder bar is transformative.

01:17:38.200 --> 01:17:40.316
Hey, Violet. Hi.
Hi.

01:17:40.520 --> 01:17:42.317
Where you going?
Doar Dorm.

01:17:42.520 --> 01:17:45.193
Fred, hi.
Hey.

01:17:49.280 --> 01:17:50.713
Good one.

01:17:51.680 --> 01:17:53.272
Oh, no.

01:18:04.000 --> 01:18:05.752
Oh, my God.

01:18:05.960 --> 01:18:09.111
I guess it wasrt realistic
to expect Doar Dorm

01:18:09.320 --> 01:18:11.515
to turn into Dior Dorm overnight.

01:18:11.720 --> 01:18:13.153
They wouldn't even open them.

01:18:13.360 --> 01:18:16.796
They said without the soap,
the discs wouldn't fly properly.

01:18:17.000 --> 01:18:20.470
Are you coming Friday?
Violet's launching her dance craze.

01:18:20.680 --> 01:18:22.033
Oh, really? That's great.

01:18:22.240 --> 01:18:24.117
What's the dance?
The Sambola.

01:18:24.320 --> 01:18:25.594
The devil's dance.

01:18:25.800 --> 01:18:29.315
Oh, cool. We'll go, right?
Yes, I'd like to.

01:18:29.520 --> 01:18:33.752
But I have several papers to finish.
But I'd like to.

01:18:51.800 --> 01:18:54.314
Great. Thanks, Gus.

01:18:54.520 --> 01:18:58.877
I don't see how we're going to start
a dance craze if no guys show up.

01:18:59.360 --> 01:19:01.999
Most guys aren't very good
with the dance-craze thing.

01:19:02.200 --> 01:19:05.112
Very good news. I was just
in my procrastination seminar

01:19:05.320 --> 01:19:08.278
and the two guys
from Doar Dorm had showered.

01:19:08.480 --> 01:19:11.517
It was clear they'd used soap.
Oh, my gosh, what a difference.

01:19:11.720 --> 01:19:15.633
Seems they'd been throwing packages
so energetically, a soap bar fell out.

01:19:15.840 --> 01:19:18.308
The unfamiliar ivory-like object
intrigued them

01:19:18.520 --> 01:19:20.829
and one thing
led to another, and, well...

01:19:21.040 --> 01:19:23.076
It was just as you said.
Isn't that great?

01:19:23.280 --> 01:19:26.192
Oh, look, here's Jimbo.
Jimbo doesn't count.

01:19:28.040 --> 01:19:29.758
Where is everybody?

01:19:38.160 --> 01:19:41.038
Arert we gonna be late
for Violet's dance craze?

01:19:41.240 --> 01:19:42.275
You wanna go to that?

01:19:42.920 --> 01:19:44.114
Yeah.

01:19:44.320 --> 01:19:47.357
You're kidding.
No, I love dance crazes.

01:19:48.600 --> 01:19:49.874
Gosh, you're strange.

01:19:50.600 --> 01:19:52.238
But aren't we already late?

01:19:52.440 --> 01:19:54.510
No, it's later on. Like 10, I think.

01:19:55.560 --> 01:19:58.996
I have to confess, I've started
losing patience with Violet.

01:19:59.200 --> 01:20:02.158
Depression calls
for serious treatment.

01:20:02.360 --> 01:20:05.193
Medication.
Psychopharmaceuticals.

01:20:05.400 --> 01:20:06.674
Talk therapy.

01:20:06.880 --> 01:20:10.316
Are those approaches effective?
Despite the medication and therapy,

01:20:10.520 --> 01:20:14.559
Ed School students are still throwing
themselves off Robertson Hall.

01:20:14.760 --> 01:20:17.399
Violet's ideas
might seem a little offbeat...

01:20:17.600 --> 01:20:21.593
A little? Oh, my God. I don't know
how much you know about Violet,

01:20:21.800 --> 01:20:23.836
but there's some
pretty weird stuff.

01:20:24.040 --> 01:20:25.917
You know, Violet. Violet Wister.

01:20:26.120 --> 01:20:27.712
It's not even her real name.

01:20:27.920 --> 01:20:30.070
It isn't?
No, it's Emily Tweeter.

01:20:30.680 --> 01:20:33.114
When she was 11,
she went completely crazy

01:20:33.320 --> 01:20:35.788
and has had several
relapses since.

01:20:36.000 --> 01:20:40.391
So it's a little worrisome to have her
counsel nearly suicidal individuals.

01:20:40.600 --> 01:20:42.318
I can't believe it.

01:20:42.520 --> 01:20:45.159
What?
Emily Tweeter.

01:20:45.360 --> 01:20:48.636
In first grade, I had an enormous crush
on a girl with that name.

01:20:49.600 --> 01:20:51.875
And you remember that?
Yeah.

01:20:53.120 --> 01:20:54.997
<i>Pretty huge Dr. Zhivago stuff.</i>

01:20:55.200 --> 01:20:58.112
Any idea or even mention of her
filled me with emotion.

01:20:58.320 --> 01:21:00.311
I had a strange perspective
on the world.

01:21:00.520 --> 01:21:02.988
I don't think my brain
was functioning properly.

01:21:03.200 --> 01:21:05.316
Everything was a bit of a dream.

01:21:06.320 --> 01:21:07.673
You think this was Violet?

01:21:07.880 --> 01:21:10.792
You have any idea if Violet
attended Willamette Montessori?

01:21:11.000 --> 01:21:12.592
In Portland?

01:21:13.120 --> 01:21:14.075
We didn't order these.

01:21:14.280 --> 01:21:16.748
Compliments of the guy at the bar.

01:21:26.760 --> 01:21:29.433
It was so brutal
how it ended between us.

01:21:30.320 --> 01:21:32.470
I know I was too angry
and a bit crazy,

01:21:32.680 --> 01:21:35.752
but I thought that what we had
was stronger than that.

01:21:35.960 --> 01:21:39.350
That you would not just walk away
after one disagreement.

01:21:40.600 --> 01:21:42.158
It wasrt just that.

01:21:42.360 --> 01:21:45.750
Oh. You mean my Cathar beliefs.

01:21:47.240 --> 01:21:48.468
Well, ahem,

01:21:50.520 --> 01:21:53.478
I am no longer a Cathar.

01:21:54.600 --> 01:21:55.715
How is that possible?

01:21:56.280 --> 01:21:58.430
It's been very difficult.

01:21:58.960 --> 01:22:01.474
You've dropped your adherence
to the Cathar faith?

01:22:01.680 --> 01:22:04.478
Yes, I have.
Good. Heh-heh.

01:22:04.680 --> 01:22:09.276
Normally I'd be reluctant to comment
on anyone's religion, but...

01:22:09.480 --> 01:22:10.879
What?

01:22:11.760 --> 01:22:14.672
I'm sorry. I guess...
I guess I'm a bit of a bigot. I just...

01:22:14.880 --> 01:22:18.953
I could never take seriously any
religion that worships on Tuesdays.

01:22:19.440 --> 01:22:23.194
Major religions require worship on the
weekend. Friday, Saturday or Sunday.

01:22:23.400 --> 01:22:25.470
I find it just really laudatory

01:22:25.680 --> 01:22:28.717
that people sacrifice
their weekend time to worship God.

01:22:30.960 --> 01:22:35.431
Having the Sabbath on Tuesday
always seemed very bizarre to me.

01:22:36.040 --> 01:22:37.917
It's not right.

01:22:38.120 --> 01:22:40.953
You know what?
We'd better get to the Lone Star.

01:22:41.640 --> 01:22:43.756
Why are you so concerned
about that?

01:22:43.960 --> 01:22:47.714
Well, it's not as if international
dance crazes start every day.

01:22:51.880 --> 01:22:53.438
We'd better hurry.

01:23:01.560 --> 01:23:03.073
What's wrong?

01:23:03.280 --> 01:23:05.350
Another fiasco.

01:23:09.880 --> 01:23:12.314
Sometimes our struggle reminds me
of the myth of Sisyphus.

01:23:12.520 --> 01:23:14.192
Who?
The myth about the guy

01:23:14.400 --> 01:23:17.597
who pushes an enormous rock
only to have it keep rolling back.

01:23:17.800 --> 01:23:19.711
Oh, yeah. What a knucklehead.

01:23:19.920 --> 01:23:22.718
The important thing to remember
is that he was mythical.

01:23:22.920 --> 01:23:25.115
He never really existed.

01:23:26.040 --> 01:23:28.759
Violet? Did you spend any part
of your education

01:23:28.960 --> 01:23:30.871
at Willamette Montessori?

01:23:31.080 --> 01:23:32.308
In Oregon?

01:23:32.960 --> 01:23:34.313
Why?

01:23:36.040 --> 01:23:38.759
Sound like "tweaker. "

01:23:38.960 --> 01:23:41.758
Would you say today is very grey?

01:23:41.960 --> 01:23:43.837
I'd say so. Maybe blue-grey.

01:23:45.160 --> 01:23:47.674
Yeah, no, that rings a bell now.

01:23:49.280 --> 01:23:50.793
Bye.

01:23:51.000 --> 01:23:54.231
I'm sorry. Her name wasrt
Emily Tweeter, but Lucy Wurlitzer.

01:23:54.440 --> 01:23:57.910
They're not similar. I'm beginning
to realise that the human memory

01:23:58.120 --> 01:24:01.112
is not the foolproof instrument
we sometimes imagine.

01:24:01.320 --> 01:24:05.154
What's worse, everyone knew about
my obsession, including my parents,

01:24:05.360 --> 01:24:07.510
those from whom
I most wanted it kept.

01:24:07.720 --> 01:24:12.669
So from your earliest years, you were
already a playboy or operator type?

01:24:12.880 --> 01:24:15.713
Yes. I suppose that's why secrecy
seemed so desirable.

